  "prompt": "I have given class 10 exam in 2014 ,and I am giving 12 exam in 2017 .am I eligible for JEE 2017 as I will appear for 1st time?",
  "response": "To be eligible for JEE Main 2017, you must have passed your 12th class examination or an equivalent qualifying examination in 2015 or 2016, or you must be appearing for the exam in 2017 for the first time. \n\nGiven that you are appearing for your 12th class examination in 2017 for the first time, you are eligible to appear for JEE Main 2017. However, you must also ensure that you meet the other eligibility criteria, such as the age limit and the minimum marks required in your qualifying examination.\n\nFor JEE Advanced 2017, the eligibility criteria are different. You must be among the top 2,20,000 candidates (including all categories) in JEE Main 2017, and you must have been born on or after October 1, 1992 (with certain relaxations for SC, ST, and PwD candidates). Additionally, you should have appeared for the Class XII (or equivalent) examination for the first time in either 2016 or 2017.\n\nPlease ensure that you check the official JEE website for the most up-to-date and accurate information regarding eligibility criteria and other requirements.",
